    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Cylinder Head and Valve Train - Installation - Fuel Injectors</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.4.11" graphiccount="8">
        <title>Fuel Injectors</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.11.1">
            <title>Replace the Fuel Injector O-rings and Copper Gasket</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air tools when installing fuel injectors. Use caution not
                        to scratch fuel injector surfaces.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, replace external O-rings and copper gasket each time the fuel
                        injector is removed.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the old copper gasket from the fuel injector with a small hand tool. Wipe fuel
                    injector nozzle with a lint free cloth.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3005104" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd11/D1131.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Replacing the copper gasket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Injector (nozzle end)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket (copper)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Deep socket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new copper injector gasket at the tip of the fuel injector. Push on with a
                    deep socket to seat gasket.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The copper gasket may be installed in either direction.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and discard the upper and lower O-rings from fuel injector using a nonmetallic
                    hand tool.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new Teflon&#174; coated (white) O-ring (smaller diameter) in the lower recess
                    just below the fuel screens. Avoid contact with sharp machined surfaces.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3005105" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd11/D1111.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel injector external O-ring locations</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring, lower (white Teflon&#174; coating) (smaller diameter)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet screens (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring, upper (black Teflon&#174; coating) (larger diameter)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp alignment slot</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring, harness connector (dark blue)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new Teflon&#174; coated (black) O-ring (larger diameter) in the recess just
                    above the fuel inlet screens. Avoid contact with sharp machined surfaces.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3005106" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D0893.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Lubricating the fuel injector O-rings</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate upper and lower O-rings with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.11.2">
            <title>Fuel Injector Assembly</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, verify hold down bolt retainer is in position when installing
                        injector hold down clamp assembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3005107" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd11/D1140.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel injector hold down clamp assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 x 45</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp alignment index</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align injector assembly clamp alignment slot with hold down clamp alignment index. This
                    will orient the injector correctly within the cylinder head.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3005108" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08010.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing fuel injector into bore</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector hold down clamp assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install fuel injector assembly by lowering fuel injector and hold down clamp assembly in
                    injector bore as one unit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3005109" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing fuel injector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector hold down clamp</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the Fuel Injector Hold Down Wrench to thread the fuel injector hold down clamp
                    assembly in the cylinder head. Do not use air powered tools to remove or install the injector. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_116.xml" xrefid="E30005C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten fuel injector hold down clamp assembly to the
                    <hotlnk document="eges3001_115.xml" xrefid="E30005B">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3005110" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installing the injector harness connector</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate connector O-ring with clean engine oil and install injector harness into
                    rocker arm carrier by pushing connector straight in until it snaps into place. Identification marks
                    should face up.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, be sure injector wiring is clear of all moving parts.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="e3005111" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ08/J08013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Lubricating top D-ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the D-ring in the top of the injector oil inlet with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
